      "text": "AMBER ALERT issued for 3-year-old Chesterfield, Va. boy Virginia State Police has issued an Amber Alert for a 3-year-old boy from Chesterfield, Va. WUSA 11:32 PM. EDT October 23, 2017   \nCHESTERFIELD, VA (WUSA9) - Virginia State Police have issued an Amber Alert for a 3-year-old boy from Chesterfield, Va. \nCayden Thomas Merchant was last seen at 6:30 p.m. on Monday on Germont Ave in North Chesterfield, Va. \nHe is described by police as a black male, 2 feet tall and weighs 29 pounds, with brown eyes and black hair. He was last seen wearing a white flannel button up shirt with orange and gray stripes. \nCayden is also described as having a scar on the left side of his head above eyebrow, a scar on left side of his nose and a scar on his right shin. \nPolice believe Cayden is in extreme danger. Cayden is likely in the custody of James Benjamin King, 40. Police say they may be riding in a red 2016 Hyundai Elantra with Virginia license plate XWS-1828. \nPicture is not of actual car but is replica of make and model \nKing is described by police as a 5'1\" black male and weighs 130 pounds. He has brown eyes and a short afro hairstyle. He was last seen wearing a Dead Pool insignia t-shirt with light-colored blue jeans. Police say they may be headed to Petersburg, Va. Anyone with information about the child, suspect &/or vehicle is asked to immediately call 911 or the Chesterfield County Police Department at 804-748-1251.",
