      "host": "news.com.au",
      "text": "Image Question time: cutting funding from the Murray Darling Basin plan 1:06 \nKate Ellis: Can the deputy Prime Minister confirm there are no documents which the government considered cutting funding from the Murray Darling Basin plan November 29th 2016 a year ago /display/newscorpaustralia.com/Web/NewsNetwork/Network News/National/ A Murray Basin Rail project worker has reportedly been killed on the job. Picture: Zoe Phillips. Source:News Corp Australia A MAN has been crushed to death by a bitumen roller after it “moved without any warning” while being loaded onto a trailer, near Mildura, in Victoria. \nA Victoria Police spokesman told news.com.au the victim was a 58-year-old Rochester man. \nNews.com.au understands the Murray Basin rail project worker died at the scene. \n“The incident happened at a landscape suppliers when a bitumen roller, which was being loaded onto a trailer, moved without any warning and pinned the man between the roller and the trailer,” a statement from Victoria Police read. \n“Police and ambulance paramedics conducted CPR on the man but he unfortunately died at the scene.” \nA Work Safe Victoria spokesperson told news.com.au it was investigating the incident. \nAmbulance Victoria has been contacted for comment. \nMore to come.",
