      "text": "Our friends at Rotoworld were pretty quick to bury Peters saying, ” It’s almost surely a season-ending injury for the 35-year-old.” Thanks for the positive vibes, guys! October 23, 2017 at 11:53 pm \nEagles fans, REDSKINS players showed a lot of class during this unfortunate play. \nNo ESPN you can leave the lame snowballs at Santa alone tonight. We (league) lost a good one……respect. October 23, 2017 at 11:56 pm \nSince the question came up… the Bills received three draft picks in the Peters trade, a 1st & 4th in 2009 & a 6th in 2010, which they used on Eric Wood, Shawn Nelson & Danny Batten, respectively. Nelson and Batten didn’t pan out, but Wood has been a starter on the OL for his entire career and was a Pro Bowl center in 2015. Given that Peters wanted out of Buffalo at the time, the trade was probably a win for both teams. bird2urmother says: \nBoysroll, skins-cowboys should be a good one next week. Dont get ahead of yourself, there. Youre not playing the 9ers again next week. Leave a Reply",
