      "title": "'Time', a Short Story by 11-Year-Old Vidwan Boon",
      "country": "US",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T04:25:07Z",
      "url": "http://www.tristanbancks.com/2017/10/time-short-story-by-11-year-old-vidwan.html",
      "host": "tristanbancks.com",
      "text": "Tuesday, October 24, 2017 'Time', a Short Story by 11-Year-Old Vidwan Boon Every now and then I read an extraordinary piece of writing by a young writer. Some of those have ended up in my books, like Indigo and Anjali 's stories. 'Time', the story below, by 11-year-old Viddy Boon is one of those extraordinary pieces. He manages to capture a lifetime and say something profound in so few words, while leaving much for discussion. I think it's an articulate and eloquent story that a writer of any age could be proud of. I hope you enjoy it. Time He had been given the watch on his tenth birthday. It was an ordinary grey plastic wristwatch in every respect except for the fact that it was counting down. 'That is all the time you have in the world son, use it wisely.'And indeed he did. As the watch ticked away, the boy, now a man, lived life to the fullest. He climbed mountains and swam oceans. He talked and laughed and lived and loved. The man was never afraid for he knew exactly how much time he had left. Eventually the watch began its final countdown. The old man looked over everything he had done, everything he had built. 5. He shook hands with his old business partner. 4. His dog came and licked his hand earning a pat on the head for his companionship. 3. He hugged his son, knowing he had been a good father. 2. He hugged his wife. 1. The old man smiled and closed his eyes.Then, nothing happened. The watch beeped once and turned off. The man stood there very much alive. You would think that in that moment he would have been overjoyed. Instead, for the first time in his life, the man was scared. By Vidwaan Boon, age 11. SHARE:",
