      "text": "By GORD YOUNG  54:39   \nReport an error \nFirefighter Chris Cuthbertson pours Halloween candy into a bin Monday at Fire Station 1 on Princess Street. North Bay Fire and Emergency Services is asking help from the community to help make its 20th annual Halloween Night for Kids a success. The department, which typically sees between 3,000 and 5,000 kids attend the event each year, is still extremely short short of wrapped candy and chips. It also needs pumpkins of all sizes, straw bales and corn stalks. Cash donations to help with displays are also appreciated. Donations can be dropped off at Station 1, or call 705-474-5662 to arrange for a pick up. The annual Halloween event is open to all ages on Oct. 31 from 5 p.m. until 8 p.m.",
