      "text": "Edan Instruments Inc (300206) Decline -0.1% on Oct 24 \nOctober 24, 2017 - By Louis Casey \nShares of Edan Instruments Inc (SHE:300206) last traded at 9.69, representing a move of -0.1%, or -0.01 per share, on volume of 6,500 shares. After opening the trading day at 9.69, shares of Edan Instruments Inc traded in a close range. Edan Instruments Inc currently has a total float of shares and on average sees shares exchange hands each day. The stock now has a 52-week low of 7.92 and high of 11.3. What Shapes Asia’s Largest Economy \nThe Asian economy is rapidly growing today and as the second biggest economy globally, China plays a big part in it. In line with this, it is important to know as well what shapes Asia’s largest country in terms of economy into a massive success. Economy rise help some companies including Edan Instruments Inc to try themselves on the big market arena. Building from the Ground Up \nThe Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE), operated by the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC), is one of China’s primary stock exchanges along with the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. In Asia, it is the second largest stock exchange. Globally, the SSE is the fifth biggest stock exchange in terms of market capitalization. Companies like Edan Instruments Inc with strong potential and good liquidity are on demand. \nThe SSE had already been founded in the 1860s. However, eventually, it had to close down in 1941 when Japan occupied Shanghai. It was reopened on November 26, 1990 and operations officially started on December 19, 1990. \nCompanies listed on the SSE are classified into two categories: 1) A shares and B shares. The main difference between the two categories is in terms of currency. A shares are traded in yuan while B shares are traded in US dollar (USD). \nBefore, only Chinese citizens were allowed to trade A shares. However, the limitation was lifted in 2002, enabling domestic and international investors to trade both A shares and B shares. With expanded opportunities for traders, the Chinese economy had since then grown faster than ever. Edan Instruments Inc had to quickly adjust. \nPre-market trading on the SSE starts at 9:15 a.m. and ends at 9:25 a.m. Regular trading starts at 9:30 a.m. and ends at 3:00 p.m. with a two-hour break that starts at 11:31 a.m. and ends at 1:29 p.m. The SSE Composite Index \nThe SSE Composite Index is the benchmark index that tracks all companies listed on the SSE. Because of its broad scope, it is composed of three sub-indices: 1) the SSE 380; 2) the SSE 180; and 3) the SSE 50. These sub-indices are intended to provide more reliable representations of the Chinese equity market given the broad nature of the SSE. \nThe SSE 380 monitors the top 380 stocks on the SSE; the SSE 180 monitors the top 180 stocks; and the SSE 50 monitors the top 50 stocks. In order for stocks to be included in the SSE 50, they first have to be included in the SSE 180; and in order for them to be included in the SSE 180, they first have to be included in the SSE 380. \nThe SSE Composite Index has a base date of December 19, 1990 and a base value of 100. Its all-time high of 6,092.06 had been recorded in October 2007 while its all-time low of 99.98 had been recorded in December 1990. \nToday is the perfect time to penetrate the Chinese equity market. There is no better way to take advantage an immense economic growth than to invest in Asia’s largest economy. With promising growth opportunities and countless potential, investors will surely enjoy the many benefits of investing on the SSE. They are curious about Edan Instruments Inc reliability. \nMore notable recent Edan Instruments Inc (SHE:300206) news were published by: Businesswire.com which released: “BIT Group Establishes IVD-Focused Contract Manufacturing Facility in China” on October 29, 2015, also Marketwired.com with their article: “Edan Introduces Acclarix LX8 Ultrasound System at MEDICA 2014 to Expand …” published on November 12, 2014, Marketwired.com published: “Edan Introduces Acclarix Compact Ultrasound System at ANESTHESIOLOGYâ„¢ 2014” on October 10, 2014. More interesting news about Edan Instruments Inc (SHE:300206) were released by: Marketwired.com and their article: “Edan Highlights Acclarix AX8 Ultrasound System at American College of Rheumatology” published on November 14, 2014 as well as Businesswire.com‘s news article titled: “BIT Group Opens IVD-Focused Contract Manufacturing Facility in China” with publication date: January 03, 2017. \nEdan Instruments, Inc. is principally engaged in the research, development, manufacture and distribution of medical electronic devices. The company has market cap of $. The Firm provides maternity product series, including doppler fetal heart beat monitors, ultrasonic doppler fetal heart beat monitors, fetal/maternal monitors and maternity integrated diagnostic monitoring systems; electrocardiograph series, including digital twelve-channel electrocardiographs, digital six-channel electrocardiographs, electrocardiographic workstations, single-channel electrocardiographs and multi-channel electrocardiographs; monitoring product series, including portable multi-variable monitors, central monitoring systems and oximeters, as well as ultrasonic image product series, including digital ultrasonic diagnostic systems and others. It currently has negative earnings. Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our daily email newsletter. Free Email Newsletter Enter your email address below to get the latest news and analysts' ratings for your stocks with our free daily email newsletter: Recent Posts",
