      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T04:33:49Z",
      "url": "http://highpointobserver.com/net-servicos-de-comunicacao-sa-netc4-is-yet-to-see-trading-action-on-oct-23/",
      "host": "highpointobserver.com",
      "text": "Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA (NETC4) Is Yet to See Trading Action on Oct 23 \nOctober 23, 2017 - By Stephen Andrade \nShares of Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA (BVMF:NETC4) closed at 0 yesterday. Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA currently has a total float of 249.66M shares and on average sees 100 shares exchange hands each day. The stock now has a 52-week low of 18.98 and high of 63.85. Ibovespa: A Witness to Brazilian Economy’s Success \nUnknown to the knowledge of many, Brazil is one of today’s fastest-growing economies and the reason behind it is a successfully emerging trade and commerce industry. Needless to say, it is a true pride of the South American economy. Brazil gives chances to a lot of big companies as Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA to receive new clients. Brazilian Mercantile and Futures (BM&F) Bovespa \nThe BM&F Bovespa is the main stock exchange in Brazil. Founded on August 23, 1890 as a public entity, it had long been under the strict supervision of the government. By the late 1960s, the government had loosened its grip on the BM&F Bovespa. \nIn 1972, electronic trading had finally been implemented to make things easier for brokers and investors alike. By the end of the decade, the Sistema Privado de Operacões por Telefone (SPOT) or the Private System of Telephone Trading, a telephone trading system, had been introduced. \nThe Mega Bolsa, an electronic trading system, had replaced the old one in 1997. Two years later, the Home Broker, an internet-based trading system that enabled individual investors to trade from home online, had been launched. \nThe BM&F Bovespa had finally been privatized as a profit entity in 2007. It officially became the BM&F Bovespa when the BM&F Exchange and the Bovespa had merged on May 8, 2008 to create a bigger and consolidated stock exchange in Brazil. Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA became one of the active participants of the trading system. \nOn August 17, 2011, the BM&F Bovespa had recorded its largest daily trading volume of $14.80 billion. On June 18, 2012, it had become one of the founding members of the Sustainable Stock Exchange initiative of the United Nations (UN). As of December 2015, more than 450 companies are listed on the BM&F Bovespa. Ibovespa Brasil Sao Paulo Stock Exchange Index \nThe Ibovespa is the benchmark index in Brazil that weighs the top 50 companies listed on the BM&F Bovespa as a market-capitalization-weighted index. \nConsequently, it represents roughly 70% of the total market capitalization on the BM&F Bovespa. Founded in 1968, it is also the oldest index measuring BM&F Bovespa companies. \nRebalancing of the Ibovespa happens quarterly to ensure its efficient representation of the trade and commerce environment in Brazil. In order for a company to become eligible for inclusion as an Ibovespa component, it must have been listed and traded on the BM&F Bovespa for not less than a calendar year prior to a particular rebalancing period. Also, more than 80% of its shares must be traded on the BM&F Bovespa to guarantee compelling activity. \nThe Ibovespa uses a base value of 100 points, which has a base date of January 2, 1968. \nThe Ibovespa had hit its all-time low of 0 in January 1972. On May 20, 2008, it had hit its all-time high of 73,516 points, which was primarily driven by a positive inflation outlook that caused major industries to surge. Nine days later, the Ibovespa had an intraday high of 73,920 points. \nInvestors must take advantage of the growth of the South American economy by investing on BM&F Bovespa stocks, especially if they are looking for meaningful long-term returns. Investors turn their attention to the Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA equities. \nMore recent Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA (BVMF:NETC4) news were published by: Seekingalpha.com which released: “Net Servicos: 4.2% Gross Return In Three Weeks With Very Low Downside Risk” on November 21, 2013. Also Theglobeandmail.com published the news titled: “Cash in on Olympics 2016 with these Brazilian stocks” on August 14, 2012. Prnewswire.com‘s news article titled: “NII Holdings Announces New President of Nextel Brazil and Appointment of Board …” with publication date: August 24, 2015 was also an interesting one. \nNet Servicos de Comunicacao SA is a Brazil firm that controls a group of cable subscription television companies. The company has market cap of $. The Firm offers cable television services under NET brand name and Internet access under NET VIRTUA brand name through several cable networks located in the country’s largest cities. It currently has negative earnings. Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA and Empresa Brasileira de Telecomunicacoes SA, a subsidiary of America Movil S.A.B. de C.V., jointly provide voice services under NET FONE VIA EMBRATEL brand name. Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our daily email newsletter. Free Email Newsletter Enter your email address below to get the latest news and analysts' ratings for your stocks with our free daily email newsletter: Recent Posts",
