      "text": "When does the 2017 World Series start? Full Astros vs. Dodgers TV schedule, live stream info Updated on October 23, 2017 at 1:36 PM Posted on October 23, 2017 at 1:31 PM Los Angeles Dodgers starting pitcher Clayton Kershaw (22) throws during the first inning of Game 5 of baseball's National League Championship Series against the Chicago Cubs, Thursday, Oct. 19, 2017, in Chicago. (AP Photo/Matt Slocum) Comment By Creg Stephenson \nThe 2017 World Series between the Houston Astros and Los Angeles Dodgers begins on Tuesday, Oct. 24. \nThe best-of-7 series features a 2-3-2 format, with Games 1 & 2 in Los Angeles. Games 3, 4 and 5 (if necessary) are set for Houston, with Games 6 & 7 (if necessary) back in L.A. \nHere's the full schedule, with TV information, live stream info and pitching matchups (all times Central): \nTuesday, Oct. 24 \nGame 1 -- Astros (Dallas Keuchel) at Dodgers (Clayton Kershaw), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) \nWednesday, Oct. 25 \nGame 2 -- Astros (Justin Verlander) at Dodgers (Rich Hill), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) \nFriday, Oct. 27 \nGame 3 -- Dodgers (Yu Darvish) at Astros (TBD), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) \nSaturday, Oct. 28 \nGame 4 -- Dodgers (TBD) at Astros (TBD), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) \nSunday, Oct. 29 \nGame 5 (if necessary) -- Dodgers (TBD) at Astros (TBD), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) \nTuesday, Oct. 31 \nGame 6 (if necessary) -- Astros (TBD) at Dodgers (TBD), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) \nWednesday, Nov. 1 \nGame 7 (if necessary) -- Astros (TBD) at Dodgers (TBD), 7 p.m., Fox ( Fox Sports Go ) View Comments",
